// Supabase.xcconfig.example — template for the app's Supabase credentials.
//
// Copy this file to `Supabase.xcconfig` (same folder), fill in the two values from
// your Supabase project (Dashboard → Project Settings → API), and wire the file into
// the target's build configurations (see docs/social-accounts-login-SETUP.md).
//
// `Supabase.xcconfig` is gitignored — the real values never get committed. The anon
// key is public-safe (it only grants what Row-Level Security allows), but keeping it
// out of git keeps project-specific config out of the repo.
//
// NOTE: xcconfig treats `//` as a comment anywhere on a line, which would eat the
// `https://` in the URL. Reference the value as `$(SUPABASE_HOST)` and rebuild the
// scheme in code (see SupabaseClientProvider) — store the host WITHOUT the scheme.

// Host only, no scheme and no trailing slash, e.g. abcdefghijklmno.supabase.co
SUPABASE_HOST = your-project-ref.supabase.co

// Project anon / public key (a long JWT starting with "eyJ...").
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY = your-anon-key-here
